q.answer:
 Use the module Bio::Tools::Run::StandAloneBlast.  It will give you access to many of the search tools in the NCBI blast suite including blastll, bl2seq, blastpgp.  The basic structure is like this.

	use Bio::Tools::Run::StandAloneBlast;
	  my $factory = Bio::Tools::Run::StandAloneBlast->new(p => 'blastn',
	                                                      d => 'nt',
                                                              e => '1e-5');
	  my $seq = new Bio::PrimarySeq(-id => 'test1',
                                        -seq => 'AGATCAGTAGATGATAGGGGTAGA');
	  my $report = $factory->blastall($seq);
